---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
const updated = "20 May 2026";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Ordina — Privacy Policy"
  description="Privacy policy for Ordina, the multi-drive file search app by DataIsland Software LLC."
>

  <section class="legal fade-in">
    <div class="breadcrumb"><a href="/privacy">← All Privacy Policies</a></div>

    <h1>Ordina — Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="meta">DataIsland Software LLC &nbsp;·&nbsp; Last updated: {updated}</p>

    <p>
      Ordina is a file search and organisation tool for macOS. This policy explains exactly what
      Ordina indexes, what leaves your device, and what is stored locally.
    </p>

    <h2>Summary</h2>
    <p>
      <strong>Ordina does not collect personal data.</strong> All file index data is stored locally
      on your Mac. Ordina has no server, no account, and no analytics. The only outbound network
      activity is OAuth authentication for cloud drive providers (credentials stored in macOS
      Keychain) and Bonjour service discovery on your local network.
    </p>

    <h2>What Ordina Indexes</h2>
    <p>
      When you add a drive, Ordina scans it and builds a local SQLite database containing:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>File and folder names</li>
      <li>File sizes and modification dates</li>
      <li>Folder hierarchy (path structure)</li>
      <li>Alias and symlink targets</li>
      <li>Tags you apply within Ordina</li>
      <li>Notes you attach within Ordina</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      Ordina <strong>does not read file contents</strong>. Documents, images, videos, and other
      files are not opened or transmitted. Only metadata is indexed.
    </p>

    <h2>Where Index Data Is Stored</h2>
    <p>
      All index databases are stored locally at:
    </p>
    <p>
      <code>~/Library/Application Support/Ordina/Volumes/</code>
    </p>
    <p>
      This data is not synced to iCloud, not transmitted to DataIsland, and not accessible
      to any third party. There is no Ordina server.
    </p>

    <h2>What Leaves Your Device</h2>

    <h3>Cloud Drive Authentication (Optional — Opt-In Only)</h3>
    <p>
      To index Google Drive, OneDrive, Dropbox, or iCloud Drive, Ordina uses OAuth
      authentication provided by each cloud service. When you connect a cloud account:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>You authenticate through an in-app browser window hosted by the cloud provider</li>
      <li>DataIsland never sees your cloud account password</li>
      <li>Access tokens are stored only in your macOS Keychain</li>
      <li>Ordina uses the provider's API to retrieve file and folder metadata (names, sizes,
        dates — not file contents)</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      Each cloud provider's privacy policy governs their handling of authentication and API calls:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" rel="noopener">Google Privacy Policy</a></li>
      <li><a href="https://privacy.microsoft.com/en-us/privacystatement" rel="noopener">Microsoft Privacy Statement</a></li>
      <li><a href="https://www.dropbox.com/privacy" rel="noopener">Dropbox Privacy Policy</a></li>
      <li><a href="https://www.apple.com/legal/privacy/" rel="noopener">Apple Privacy Policy (iCloud)</a></li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Bonjour — Local Network Only</h3>
    <p>
      Ordina uses Apple's Bonjour protocol on your local network (LAN) for two purposes:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Ordina Agent discovery</strong> — when the Ordina Agent is running on another
        machine on your network, Ordina discovers it automatically via Bonjour. No data is sent
        to the internet.</li>
      <li><strong>Pro licence broadcast</strong> (Ordina Pro only) — Ordina broadcasts a hash of
        your purchase receipt on the LAN to enforce single-machine licensing. This hash contains
        no personal information. No data is sent to the internet.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      Bonjour traffic stays entirely within your local network. It is not routed to the internet.
    </p>

    <h2>Ordina Agent</h2>
    <p>
      The Ordina Agent is a command-line tool that runs on a remote machine on your local network.
      It builds an index database and broadcasts its availability via Bonjour. All communication
      between the Agent and Ordina occurs on your local network only. No data is sent to DataIsland
      or to any internet server.
    </p>

    <h2>Full Disk Access</h2>
    <p>
      Ordina requests Full Disk Access (FDA) to index external drives and paths outside your
      home folder. FDA is used solely to read file metadata for indexing. Ordina does not read
      file contents, modify files, or transmit files or file contents to any server.
    </p>

    <h2>What Ordina Does Not Do</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Does not read or transmit file contents</li>
      <li>Does not send index data to DataIsland or any internet server</li>
      <li>Does not require an account or login</li>
      <li>Does not collect analytics or send crash reports to DataIsland</li>
      <li>Does not share any data with third parties for advertising</li>
      <li>Does not sync index databases to iCloud or any cloud service</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Children's Privacy</h2>
    <p>
      Ordina is not directed at children under 13. We do not knowingly collect information
      from children.
    </p>

    <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
    <p>
      If we make material changes to this policy, we will update the "Last updated" date above.
      Continued use of Ordina after changes constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Questions about this policy:
      <br />
      <a href="mailto:support@dataisland.com">support@dataisland.com</a>
      <br />
      DataIsland Software LLC
    </p>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .legal {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 3rem 0 5rem;
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  .breadcrumb { margin-bottom: 2rem; font-size: 0.9rem; }
  .legal h1 { font-size: 2.1rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .meta { font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--gray); margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  .legal h2 { margin-top: 2.25rem; margin-bottom: 0.6rem; font-size: 1.2rem; }
  .legal h3 { margin-top: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 600; }
  .legal p  { font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 0.9rem; }

  code {
    background: var(--gray-light);
    padding: 0.15em 0.4em;
    border-radius: 4px;
    font-size: 0.9em;
  }

  ul { margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 1.25rem; color: var(--gray-dark); }
  ul li { margin-bottom: 0.4rem; font-size: 0.97rem; line-height: 1.5; }
</style>
